<br />
<br /> But that's kinda far off spec for the NTSC realm of timings. There's no guarantee all/most sets will be able to output that signal - analog or not. Hell, I've seen NTSC sets that <em>won't</em> even show PS or SNES video correctly (weird jumping of the screen) from the 80's but sets of the 70's (and 90's+) that show them just fine.

		

